Euro-Area Ministers May Get Additional Staff, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-09-11T14:03:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-11/euro-area-ministers-may-get-additional-staff-handelsblatt-says.html
Euro-area finance ministers will be
given extra administrative staff in Brussels and likely be
represented by a full-time chairman from mid-2012,  Handelsblatt 
reported, citing unidentified European diplomats.  Candidates to succeed Luxembourg Prime Minister  Jean-Claude Juncker , who currently leads the euro-area group, include
Spanish Finance Minister  Elena Salgado  and European Union
President  Herman Van Rompuy , the newspaper said in an article to
be published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer in Berlin at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at 
 cthomas16@bloomberg.net  